{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "brenton:job.29",
    "translationId": "brenton",
    "bookSlug": "job",
    "chapterNumber": 29,
    "referenceLabel": "Job 29",
    "summary": "Source text for Job 29 in Brenton Septuagint."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.1",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:1",
      "text": "And Job continued and said in his parable,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.2",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:2",
      "text": "Oh that I were as in months past, wherein God preserved me!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.3",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:3",
      "text": "As when his lamp shone over my head; when by his light I walked through darkness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.4",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:4",
      "text": "As when I steadfastly pursued my ways, when God took care of my house.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.5",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:5",
      "text": "When I was very fruitful, and my children were about me;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.6",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:6",
      "text": "when my ways were moistened with butter, and the mountains flowed for me with milk.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.7",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:7",
      "text": "When I went forth early in the city, and the seat was placed for me in the streets.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.8",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:8",
      "text": "The young men saw me, and hid themselves: and all the old men stood up.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.9",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:9",
      "text": "And the great men ceased speaking, and laid their finger on their mouth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.10",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:10",
      "text": "And they that heard me blessed me, and their tongue clave to their throat.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.11",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:11",
      "text": "For the ear heard, and blessed me; and the eye saw me, and turned aside.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.12",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:12",
      "text": "For I saved the poor out of the hand of the oppressor, and helped the fatherless who had no helper.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.13",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:13",
      "text": "Let the blessing of the perishing one come upon me; yea, the mouth of the widow has blessed me.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.14",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:14",
      "text": "Also I put on righteousness, and clothed myself with judgment like a mantle.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.15",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:15",
      "text": "I was the eye of the blind, and the foot of the lame.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.16",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:16",
      "text": "I was the father of the helpless; and I searched out the cause which I knew not.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.17",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:17",
      "text": "And I broke the jaw-teeth of the unrighteous; I plucked the spoil out of the midst of their teeth.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.18",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:18",
      "text": "And I said, My age shall continue as the stem of a palm-tree; I shall live a long while.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.19",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:19",
      "text": "My root was spread out by the water, and the dew would lodge on my crop.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.20",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:20",
      "text": "My glory was fresh in me, and my bow prospered in his hand.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.21",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:21",
      "text": "Men heard me, and gave heed, and they were silent at my counsel.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.22",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:22",
      "text": "At my word they spoke not again, and they were very glad whenever I spoke to them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.23",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 23,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:23",
      "text": "As the thirsty earth expecting the rain, so they waited for my speech.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.24",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 24,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:24",
      "text": "Were I to laugh on them, they would not believe it; and the light of my face has not failed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "brenton:job.29.25",
      "translationId": "brenton",
      "bookSlug": "job",
      "chapterNumber": 29,
      "verseNumber": 25,
      "referenceLabel": "Job 29:25",
      "text": "I chose out their way, and sat chief, and dwelt as a king in the midst of warriors, as one comforting mourners.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
